NAME		roff  --  format text
.sp
.ti 0
.nf
SYNOPSIS	roff____ [ +_number ] [ -_number ] name\d1\u ...
.fi
.sp
.ti 0
DESCRIPTION	roff____
formats text according to control lines embedded in the text.
The optional argument "+number" causes printing
to begin at the first page
with the appropriate number;
"-number" causes printing to cease
at the first page with a higher number.
.sp
roff____ is fully described in a separate publication [reference].
.sp
.ti 0
FILES		/etc/suftab___________
contains a list of suffixes used to guide hyphenation.
/tmp/rtma, rtmb, ... temporary.
/dev/ttyn to suspend messages.
.sp
.ti 0
SEE ALSO	[reference], mesg
.sp
.ti 0
DIAGNOSTICS	none -- files not found are ignored
.sp
.ti 0
BUGS		roff____
does not check for various kinds of buffer overflow.
If a fault occurs, check the input in the region
where the error occured
